title: A Night at the Opera
overview: A sly business manager and two wacky friends of two opera singers help them achieve success while humiliating their stuffy and snobbish enemies.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

title: Breakfast at Tiffany's
overview: A young New York socialite becomes interested in a young man who has moved into her apartment building, but her past threatens to get in the way.

title: The Graduate
overview: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: The Circus
overview: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus.

title: The Purple Rose of Cairo
overview: In New Jersey in 1935, a movie character walks off the screen and into the real world.

title: A Hard Day's Night
overview: Over two "typical" days in the life of The Beatles, the boys struggle to keep themselves and Sir Paul McCartney's mischievous grandfather in check while preparing for a live television performance.

title: Bringing Up Baby
overview: While trying to secure a $1 million donation for his museum, a befuddled paleontologist is pursued by a flighty and often irritating heiress and her pet leopard, Baby.

title: Roman Holiday
overview: A bored and sheltered princess escapes her guardians and falls in love with an American newsman in Rome.

title: The Philadelphia Story
overview: When a rich woman's ex-husband and a tabloid-type reporter turn up just before her planned remarriage, she begins to learn the truth about herself.

title: (500) Days of Summer
overview: An offbeat romantic comedy about a woman who doesn't believe true love exists, and the young man who falls for her.

title: Vicky Donor
overview: A man is brought in by an infertility doctor to supply him with his sperm, where he becomes the biggest sperm donor for his clinic.

title: Rushmore
overview: The extracurricular king of Rushmore Preparatory School is put on academic probation.

title: Marriage Story
overview: Noah Baumbach's incisive and compassionate look at a marriage breaking up and a family staying together.

title: City Lights
overview: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.

title: Annie Hall
overview: Neurotic New York comedian Alvy Singer falls in love with the ditzy Annie Hall.

title: Charade
overview: Romance and suspense ensue in Paris as a woman is pursued by several men who want a fortune her murdered husband had stolen. Whom can she trust?

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Crna macka, beli macor
overview: Matko and his son Zare live on the banks of the Danube river and get by through hustling and basically doing anything to make a living. In order to pay off a business debt Matko agrees to marry off Zare to the sister of a local gangster.
